Scope `linearis issues list` to actionable pickup candidates: exclude issues
explicitly assigned to other people, while still surfacing unassigned issues
and my own. Keeps the existing "not completed" filter and updatedAt ordering.

Used by rig's no-arg `up` picker, which lists the 25 most recently updated
issues; without this filter a busy teammate's issues crowd out mine. `isMe`
resolves against the API token server-side, so no extra identity lookup.

This is a local behavior change with no upstream PR; it's opinionated for a
single-user workflow and unlikely to be accepted upstream as a default.

--- a/src/queries/issues.ts
+++ b/src/queries/issues.ts
@@ -26,6 +26,10 @@ export const GET_ISSUES_QUERY = `
       orderBy: $orderBy
       filter: {
         state: { type: { neq: "completed" } }
+        or: [
+          { assignee: { null: true } }
+          { assignee: { isMe: { eq: true } } }
+        ]
       }
     ) {
       nodes {
